/* Java Program to Remove All Whitespaces from a String*\

public class RemoveWhitespace {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String input = "  Java   Programming   Language  ";
        String result = input.replaceAll("\\s", ""); // Remove all whitespaces
        System.out.println("Original String: " + input);
        System.out.println("String without whitespaces: " + result);
    }
}
Output:
Original String:   Java   Programming   Language  
String without whitespaces: JavaProgrammingLanguage

The program uses the replaceAll() method with the regex \\s, which matches any whitespace character (spaces, tabs, etc.).
It replaces all such matches with an empty string, effectively removing all whitespaces from the input string.
